[
  "Bang Jun-hyuk is the chairman of South Korea's largest mobile-gaming company, Netmarble, which he founded in 2000.",
  "He's built Netmarble into a $2 billion gaming empire with its action-packed role-playing games that have become hits across Asia and the U.S. ",
  "In May 2017, he took the company public, raising $2.4 billion in what became South Korea's largest listing in seven years. "
